Lab 7 Files:

Assignment:
CSC3320 System Level Programming 
Lab Assignment 7 - Post-Lab 
Due at 11:59 pm on Friday, March 5, 2021 
Purpose: Learn how to get input and print out formatted results  using scanf and printf separately in C. 

Part 1: 
1) Write a C program named as getPhoneNumber.c that prompts the user to  enter a telephone number in the form (999)999-9999 and then displays the  number in the form 999-999-999: 
Enter phone number [(999)999-9999]: (404)123-4567  You entered 404-123-4567 
Question: Execute your getPhoneNumber.c and attach a screenshot of the output. Then write the source code of getPhoneNumber.c in your answer sheet and upload your file  getPhoneNumber.c to googleClassroom. 

2) Write a program named as calcPrice.c that formats product information  entered by the user and calculate the total amount of purchase. 
Enter item number:583 
Enter unit price:13.5 
Enter quantity:2 
Enter purchase date (mm/dd/yyyy):09/15/2016 
Item Unit Price QTY Purchase Date Total Amount 583 $ 13.50 2 9/15/2016 $ 27.00 
The item number, quantity and date should be left justified; the unit price and  total amount should be right justified. Hint: Use tabs to line up the columns. Question: Execute your calcPrice.c and attach a screenshot of the output. Then write the 
source code of calcPrice.c in your answer sheet and upload your file calcPrice.c to  classroom. 

Part 2: (Optional) 
Note : This part is not for grading. But you will get some feedback. Can you write a shell script to finish the same task as in question 1) of Part 1? 
